<h1>Standard Data Products - Processed List</h1>
<p></p>
<h2>As of Feb 23, 1995</h2>
<p></p>
<p>This list of processed standard data products are sorted by datatake id.  The
following abbreviations are used :  DT is DataTake, GMT is Greenwich Mean
Time, Lat is  the center Latitude in decimal degrees, Lon is the center Longitude in decimal
degrees, L PR# is the L-band Processing Run Number, C PR# is the C-band
Processing Run Number, and PDT is the Product Data Type (eg. SLC, MLC,
MLD, GEOC)</p>
<p>This list includes both SRL-1 and SRL-2;  you can tell by the GMT, if
it is in the 100's then it is SRL-1, if it is in the 200's then it is
SRL-2</p>
<p>For some datatakes, we do not list the center lat/lon.We will try to
update this list every couple of months.</p>
<p>This list does not include survey processed data which may be found
at the <a href="http://sun1.cr.usgs.gov/landdaac/sir-c/sir-c.html">EROS Data Center</a></p>
<pre>
<hr>
