<html><head><!-- This document was created from RTF source by rtftohtml version
2.7.3 --><title>License agreement 3/28/95</title></head><body
bgcolor="#ffffff"><b>ABSTRACT</b><p>
<b></b><p>
The <b>CEOS Reader Software Package</b> contains the following software:<p>
<p>
- CEOS_READER which reads SIR-C data from tape, copies data to disk, reads
headers and outputs ASCII header files to disk.<p>
<p>
- DCOMP contains subroutines for decompression and recompression of SIR-C data.
For any format SIR-C data or AIRSAR format data, DCOMP will synthesize any
polarization from quad pol data or a given polarization from dual and single
pol data to a byte image.  DCOMP also multilooks data to the desired amount.<p>
<p>
- CVERT software which converts data between different AIRSAR and SIR-C data
formats.  CVERT also multilooks data to the desired amount.<p>
<p>
- SIRC-REG software displays and co-registers SIR-C, XSAR, AIRSAR, and byte
image data with and IDL graphical interface.<p>
<p>
- RAVEN software runs with an IDL graphical interface and synthesizes any
polarization from quad pol data, and calculates polarization signatures,
performs statistical analysis.  RAVEN works with both SIR-C and AIRSAR format
data.<p>
<p>
<p>
The <b>SIRC Utilities Software</b>, which is part of the CEOS Reader Software
Package, is written in IDL and includes the following programs:<p>
<p>
- SIRC_Synth:  Image synthesis from decompressed SIR-C data.  Allows the user
to synthesize trial byte images using subsampled data.  When the user approves
the look of the trial image, an image is synthesized from the original data.<p>
<p>
- SIRC_GetImgInf:  Prints out the number of samples, number of records, data
format and mode given the SIRC ascii header.<p>
<p>
- SIRC_Extract:  Draw polygons on a SIR-C image.  Compute stats on values
inside the polygons.<p>
<p>
- ViewByte:  Display a byte image.  Scales the image to fit on the screen if
necessary.<p>
<p>
- ViewRGB:  Displays a 3 color overlay given three byte images.  Scales the
image to fit the screen if necessary.<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
