<html><head><!-- This document was created from RTF source by rtftohtml version2.7.3 --></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff"><b>JPL Conversion Tools and Analysis/Display Software forSIR-C/XSAR and AIRSAR Data</b><p><b></b><p><p><b>CEOS_READER</b>	Reads SIR-C data from tape, copies data to disk, readsheaders and outputs ASCII header files to disk.  Runs on unix and VMScomputers.<p><p><b>DCOMP</b>	Subroutines for decompression and recompression of SIR-C data.For any format SIR-C data, or AIRSAR format data, synthesizes any polarizationfrom quad pol data or a given polarization from dual and single pol data to abyte image. Multilooks data to desired amount.  Runs on unix and VMScomputers.<p><p><b>CVERT</b>	Converts between different AIRSAR and SIR-C data formats.Multilooks data to desired amount.  Runs on unix and VMS computers.<p><p><b>SIRC-REG</b>	Displays and co-registers SIR-C, XSAR, AIRSAR, and byte imagedata with IDL graphical interface.  Runs on SUN computers with IDL.<p><p><b>RAVEN</b>	IDL graphical interface, synthesizes any polarization from quadpol data, calculates polarization signatures, performs statistical analysis.Works with both SIR-C and AIRSAR format data.  Full functionality with SIR-Cdata is forthcoming. Runs on SUN computers with IDL. <p><p><b>MACSIGMA0</b>	Displays AIRSAR, JERS-1, Magellan, and byte data.  Analyzescorner reflectors, performs statistical analysis, and zooms in to data.  Runson Macintosh computers with 8 bit graphics.  This software is available throughCOSMIC.<p><p><b>POLCAL</b>	Calibration and calibration verification of AIRSAR data.Analysis of corner reflectors and distributed targets.  Correction to AIRSARantenna pattern errors due to errors in altitude or roll.  Topographiccalibrations may be performed.  Will soon be available for calibration andcalibration verification of SIR-C data.  This software is available throughCOSMIC.<p><p><p><b>FOR INSTRUCTIONS ON OBTAINING SOFTWARE, PLEASE CONTACT ELLEN O'LEARY BY MAILAT  THE JET PROPULSION LABORATORY, MAIL STOP 300-233, 4800 OAK GROVE, PASADENA,CALIFORNIA 91109</b><p><b></b><p><p><b>SAR Data Formats</b><p><b></b><p><b>SIR-C MLC</b>	SIR-C Multilook Complex data is quad or dual pol compressedcross products of the Stokes Matrix.  Generally converted to ground rangeprojection.<p><p><b>SIR-C MLD</b>	SIR-C Multilook Detected is single pol multilook powerdetected data, 8 bit mantissa, 8 bit exponent.  Generally converted to groundrange projection.<p><p><b>SIR-C SLC</b>	SIR-C Singlelook Complex is quad, dual, or single polcompressed scattering matrix data  Generally in the slant range projection.<p><p><b>XSAR</b> 	XSAR Multilook Detected data, 16 bit unsigned integer, singlepol.<p><p><b>AIRSAR CM	</b>AIRSAR quad pol compressed Stokes matrix data.  Generally inthe slant range projection.  Similar to SIR-C MLC.<p></body></html>
