<TITLE>SIR-C Radar Images</TITLE>
<H1>SIR-C Radar Images</H1>
<HR>
<P><a href="desc/SIRCdesc.html">SIR-C</a> flew on-board the Space Shuttle
Endeavour twice in 1994 (April and October).  It is a dual frequency
(L-band and C-band), multipolarization radar.

<HR>
<UL><B><LI><A HREF="sircdvimages.html">SIR-C flight 1 (STS-59) images of
Death Valley, California</A></LI>
</P><P>
</B></UL>
<hr>
<p>Here is a <A HREF="jpeg/sircmaps/srl1.jpg">map of the acquired coverage</a> 
by <a href="desc/SIRCdesc.html">SIR-C/XSAR</a>
during flight 1 (S-59) in April, 1994</p>
<p></p>
<HR>
<A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="gif/icons/back-yellow.gif"
ALIGN=BOTTOM></A>     Imaging Radar Home Page
