<TITLE>Magellan Radar Images</TITLE>
<H1>Magellan Radar Images</H1>
<HR>
<P><a href="mgndesc.html">Magellan</a> is an 
imaging radar that was sent to the planet Venus to map the
surface beneath the visibly opaque cloud layer.
</p> 
<HR>
<p>The <A
HREF="http://delcano.mit.edu/cgi-bin/midr-query"> Magellan Image
Browser</A> is now accepting connections at the <A
HREF="http://delcano.mit.edu/">Microwave Subnode</A> of NASA's <A
HREF="http://stardust.jpl.nasa.gov/pds_home.html">Planetary Data
System</A>. Tour the planet <I>Venus</I> during your lunch break.  So
little time, so much data!
</p>
<p> The <a href="http://newproducts.jpl.nasa.gov/magellan/mgn.html">Magellan Mission to Venus </a>
(JPL) Home Page is now online!</p>
