7	13-28	A16	---	---	Spare<p>
8	29-60	A32	PF/OPS	pdata_product<p>
				pspecial_product<p>
				pmap_projection	Map projection descriptor (MLD, MLC: "GROUND$RANGE$$$...",
SLC, RSD: "SLANT$RANGE$$$...", GEC, GTC: "UTM", "SSMI", or "UPS")<p>
9	61-76	I16	PF	pdigital_pixels<p>
				pprfc_samp<p>
				pgec_pixels	Number of pixels per line of image<p>
10	77-92	I16	PF	pdigital_lines<p>
				ptotal_rg_lines<p>
				pgec_lines	Number of lines<p>
11	93-108	F16.7	PF	prg_spacing<p>
				pgec_pixel_spacing	Nominal inter-pixel distance in output scene (meters)<p>
12	109-124	F16.7	PF	paz_spacing<p>
				pgec_pixel_spacing	Nominal inter-line distance in output scene (meters)<p>
13	125-140	F16.7	---	---	Orientation at output scene center, for geocoded
products this is simply the convergence of the meridians, ie. the angle between
geographic north and map grid north (degrees) (Angle of projection axis from
true North)<p>
14	141-156	F16.7	---	---	Actual platform orbital inclination (degrees)<p>
15	157-172	F16.7	---	---	Actual ascending node (longitude at equator)
(degrees)<p>
16	173-188	F16.7	PF	pdistance_scene_ctr	Distance of platform at input scene
center from the geocenter (km)<p>
17	189-204	F16.7	PF	paltitude_geodetic	Geodedic altitude of the platform
relative to the ellipsoid (km)<p>
18	205-220	F16.7	PF	pnadir_spd_scene_ctr	Actual ground speed at nadir at input
scene center time (km/sec)<p>
19	221-236	F16.7	PF	pnadir_trk_ang_scene_ctr	Platform heading (degrees):
effective subplatform track direction angle relative to true north, including
the effects of orbital inclination and skew due to earth rotation.<p>
<p>
