<p>
COEFFS. FOR IMAGE TO MAP TO IMAGE CONVERSION<p>
<p>
80-87	1265-1424	8E20.10	PF/OPS	ptop_left_long<p>
				pgec_pixel_spacing<p>
				ptop_left_lat	Eight coefficients (A11, A12,...,A24) to convert a line (L)
and pixel (P) position to the map projection frame of reference, say (E,N)
where:<p>
						E = A11 + A12 + A13 + A14TL<p>
						N = A21 + A22 + A23 + A24nP<p>
88-95	1425-1584	8E20.10	PF/OPS	ptop_left_long<p>
				pgec_pixel_spacing	Eight coefficients (B11, B12,...,B24) to convert from
the map projection (E,N) to line (l) and pixel (P) position in the image, say
(L,P) where:<p>
				---		L = B11 + B12 + B13 + B144ETN<p>
				---		P = B21 + B22TE + B23TN<p>
96	1585-1620	A36	---	---	Spares<p>
<p>
NOTES for fields 80-95:<p>
<p>
	Easting	= A11 + A12 * line + A13 * column + A14 * line * column<p>
	Northing 	= A21 + A22 * line + A23 * column + A24 * line * column<p>
<p>
The inverse is computed by:<p>
<p>
	Line	= B11 + B12 * East + B13 * North + B14 * North * East<p>
	Column	= B21 + B22 * East + B23 * North + B24 * North * East<p>
<p>
Because of the cartesic mapping systems used for UTM and UPS, coefficients A12,
A14, A23, A24, B12, B14, B23, B24 are all 0.<p>
<b>SAR Leader File:</b><p>
<b>
<a name="RTFToC16">Platform
Position Record
</a></b><p>
<b></b><p>
 The format of the record is defined below.  (One record with a variable number
of data sets.)<p>
<p>
<b>Field	Bytes	Format	Source	Parameter	Description</b><p>
<b></b><p>
1	1-4	B4	OPS	---	Sequence number (4)<p>
2	5	Bl	OPS	---	lst record subtype code (10)<p>
3	6	Bl	OPS	---	Record type code (30)<p>
4	7	Bl	OPS	---	2nd record subtype code (50)<p>
5	8	B1	OPS	---	3rd record subtype code (20)<p>
6	9-12	B4	OPS	---	Length of this record (variable)<p>
<p>
7	13-44	A32	---	---	Orbital elements designator <p>
8	45-60	F16.7	---	---	lst orbital element<p>
9	61-76	F16.7	---	---	2nd orbital element<p>
10	77-92	F16.7	---	---	3rd orbital element<p>
11	93-108	F16.7	---	---	4th orbital element<p>
12	109-124	F16.7	---	---	5th orbital element<p>
13	125-140	F16.7	---	---	6th orbital element<p>
14	141-144	I4	EPH/OPS	---	Number of data sets<p>
15	145-148	I4	EPH/OPS	---	Year of data point (YYYY) for first point<p>
16	149-152	I4	EPH/OPS	---	Month of data point (MM) for first point<p>
17	153-156	I4	EPH/OPS	---	Day of data point (DD) for first point<p>
18	157-160	I4	EPH/OPS	---	Days of the year (GMT) for first point<p>
19	161-182	D22.15	EPH/OPS	---	Seconds of day (GMT) for first point<p>
20	183-204	D22.15	EPH/OPS	---	Time interval between data sets (data points)
(sec)<p>
21	205-268	A64	PF/OPS	pcoordinate_state	Reference coordinate system for state
vector and attitude vector ("GREENWHICH$TRUE$OF$DATE" or "EARTH$CENTERED" if
geocoded product)<p>
22	269-290	D22.15	CONST	paries_hour_angle	Angle between +x-axis of coordinate
system and the Prime Meridian (degrees)<p>
23	291-306	F16.7	---	---	Along track position error (meters)<p>
24	307-322	F16.7	---	---	Across track position error (meters)<p>
25	323-338	F16.7	---	---	Radial position error (meters/sec)<p>
26	339-354	F16.7	---	---	Along track velocity error (meters/sec)<p>
27	355-370	F16.7	---	---	Across track velocity error (meters/sec)<p>
28	371-386	F16.7	---	---	Radial velocity error (meters/sec)<p>
29	387-388	A2	---	---	Spare<p>
<p>
PLATFORM POSITION DATA SET<p>
<p>
30	389-454	3D22.15	EPH	---	1st data point (X,Y,Z) position vector (km)<p>
31	455-520	3D22.15	EPH	---	1st data point (X,Y,Z) velocity vector  (km/sec)<p>
<p>
Repeat fields 29-30 for each record in the ephemeris file.<p>
