<p>
<b>SAR Leader File:</b><p>
<b>
<a name="RTFToC18">Radiometric
Data Record
</a></b><p>
<b></b><p>
The radiometric data record is defined below.   (One record per polarization
channel.  For SIR-C implementation, one data set per record.)<p>
<p>
<b>Field	Bytes	Format	Source	Parameter	Description</b><p>
<b></b><p>
1	1-4	B4	OPS	---	Sequence number (6)<p>
2	5	Bl	OPS	---	Record subtype code (10)<p>
3	6	Bl	OPS	---	Record type code (50)<p>
4	7	Bl	OPS	---	2nd record subtype code (50)<p>
5	8	Bl	OPS	---	3rd record subtype code (20)<p>
6	9-12	B4	OPS	---	Length of this record (144)<p>
<p>
7	13-16	I4	OPS	---	Radiometric data record sequence number (1, 2, ...)<p>
8	17-20	I4	OPS	---	Number of radiometric data sets in the record (1)<p>
9	21-24	A4	---	---	Padding for word boundary<p>
<p>
RADIOMETRIC DATA SET<p>
<p>
10	25-32	I8	OPS	---	Radiometric data set size in bytes<p>
11	33-36	A4	PF/OPS	pfrequency,<p>
				ppolarization	SAR channel indicator ("XVV$","LHH$", "LHV$", "LVV$", "LVH$",
"CHH$", "CHV$", "CVV$", "CVH$")<p>
12	37-40	A4	---	---	Spare<p>
13	41-64	A24	CAL_QA	qcal_date	Date of nearest calibration update (yymmdd) <p>
14	65-72	I8	OPS	---	Number of samples in the look up table (0)<p>
15	73-88	A16	PF/OPS	pdata_product	Sample type designator (MLD, MLC:
"CROSS$PRODUCTS"; SLC: "SCATTERING$MATRIX"; RSD: "NONE")<p>
<p>
					Calibration Equation:<p>
						&lt;I&gt; = K * s<sup>0</sup>  + KN(R) * &lt;N&gt;<p>
					where<p>
					 &lt;I&gt;		: expectation value of image pixel power<p>
					K			: absolute calibration constant<p>
					KN(R)	: noise gain of processor as a function of range R<p>
					&lt;N&gt;		: raw data noise power per sample<p>
16	89-104	F16.7	PF	phh_noise_power<p>
				phv_noise_power<p>
				pvv_noise_power<p>
				pvh_noise_power	Raw data noise power estimate (&lt;N&gt;) (data number
units)<p>
17	105-120	F16.7	OPS	---	Linear conversion factor (backscatter coefficient to
image power conversion factor) (K) (1)<p>
18	121-136	F16.7	PF	pnoise_gain	Processor gain for noise data before
radiometric correction is applied. (KN,0)<p>
19	137-140	A4	---	---	Spare<p>
20	141-144	A4	---	---	Padding for word boundary<p>
<p>
<p>
The CEOS file definition for the Radiometric Data Record includes a variable
length look up table following field 20.  Since the SIR-C implementaion does
not include the look up table, there is only one data set in each Radiometric
Data Record and each record is of fixed length.<p>
<p>
<p>
