<b>SAR Leader File:</b><p>
<b>
<a name="RTFToC21">Data
Histograms Record
</a></b><p>
<b></b><p>
Histograms shall be generated for image and signal data files. One histogram
record is generated per polarization.  Two data sets are included in each
record: one for raw data and one for image data.  When working with a
Reformatted Signal Data data product, no image histogram is provided.<p>
<p>
<b>Field	Bytes	Format	Source	Parameter	Description</b><p>
<b></b><p>
1	1-4	B4	OPS	---	Sequence number (9)<p>
2	5	Bl	OPS	---	lst record subtype code (10)<p>
3	6	Bl	OPS	---	Record type code (70)<p>
4	7	Bl	OPS	---	2nd record subtype code (50)<p>
5	8	Bl	OPS	---	3rd record subtype code (20)<p>
6	9-12	B4	OPS	---	Length of this record (variable, depends on whether image
histogram data set is provided)<p>
<p>
7	13-16	I4	OPS	---	Data histograms record sequence number <p>
8	17-20	A4	PF/OPS	pfrequency,<p>
				ppolarization	SAR channel indicator("XVV$", "LHH$", "LHV$", "LVV$", "LVH$",
"CHH$", "CHV$", "CVV$", "CVH$")<p>
9	21-28	I8	PF/OPS	pdata_product	Number of histogram table data sets in this
record (2: one raw data histogram and one image data histogram, except RSD
product) <p>
10	29-36	I8	OPS	---	Histogram table data set size in bytes<p>
11	37-40	A4	---	---	Padding for word boundary<p>
<p>
HISTOGRAM DATA SET <p>
<p>
12	41-72	A32	OPS	---	Histogram descriptor ("RAW$DATA$$$$$..."or
"IMAGE$DATA$$$$$...")<p>
13	73-76	I4	OPS	---	Number of histogram records needed to reconstitute the full
histogram table (1)<p>
14	77-80	I4	OPS	---	Sequence number in the full histogram table of the table
contained in this record (1)<p>
15	81-88	I8	QA_PARM/OPS	qraw_hist_size,<p>
				qimg_hist_size	Histogram table size, in bytes<p>
16	89-96	I8	PF	pprfc_samp,<p>
				pdigital_pixels	Total number of samples/pixels per line<p>
17	100-104	I8	PF	ptotal_rg_lines,<p>
				pdigital_lines	Total number of image lines <p>
18	105-112	I8	QA_PARM	qraw_samp_per_group,<p>
				qimg_samp_per_group	Data samples/pixels per group in cross track<p>
19	113-120	I8	QA_PARM	qraw_lines_per_group,<p>
				qimg_lines_per_group	Data lines per group in along track<p>
20	121-128	I8	QA_PARM	qraw_xtrack_num_groups,<p>
				qimg_xtrack_num_groups<p>
					Number of groups cross track<p>
21	129-136	I8	QA_PARM	qraw_atrack_num_groups,<p>
				qimg_atrack_num_groups<p>
					Number of groups along track <p>
<p>
DATA STATISTICS<p>
<p>
22	137-152	F16.7	QA_PARM/OPS	qimg_hist_minval	Minimum sample value
corresponding to first histogram table bin<p>
23	153-168	F16.7	QA_PARM/OPS	pbits_per_sample,<p>
				qimg_hist_maxval	Maximum sample value corresponding to last histogram table
bin<p>
24	169-184	F16.7	QA_PARM	qraw_hist_mean_global,<p>
				qimg_hist_mean_global<p>
					Mean sample value<p>
25	185-200	F16.7	QA_PARM	qraw_hist_sd_global,<p>
				qimg_hist_sd_global	Standard deviation of sample value<p>
26	201-216	F16.7	OPS	---	Sample value increment<p>
<p>
DATA HISTOGRAM STATISTICS<p>
<p>
27	217-232	F16.7	OPS	---	Minimum histogram table value<p>
28	233-248	F16.7	OPS	---	Maximum histogram table value<p>
29	249-264	F16.7	---	---	Mean histogram table value<p>
30	265-280	F16.7	---	---	Standard deviation of histogram table<p>
31	281-288	I8	QA_PARM	qraw_hist_size,<p>
				qimg_hist_size	Number of bins<p>
32	289-296	F16.7	QA_PLOT	qraw_hist_data<p>
				qimg_hist_data	lst histogram table value<p>
33	297-312	F16.7	QA_PLOT	qraw_hist_data<p>
				qimg_hist_data	2nd histogram table value<p>
34-n	313-m	(n-2)F16.7	QA_PLOT	qraw_hist_data<p>
				qimg_hist_data	3rd to nth histogram table value<p>
